# LayoutForge (manu2print) – Stack & Conventions

## Stack
- **Next.js 15** (App Router), React 19, TypeScript. Hosted on **Vercel**.
- **Supabase** for auth, storage metadata, email_captures, subscriptions, payments (Lemon Squeezy webhooks).
- **CloudConvert** for paid flows only (keyword/description PDF→text, EPUB; not used for free PDF Compressor or Print Optimizer).
- **Anthropic (Claude)** for AI: keyword research, description generator, future Format Review. Use Haiku for cost-sensitive flows.
- **pdf-lib**, **pdfjs-dist** (client-side), **docx**, **JSZip**, **mammoth** for PDF/DOCX handling.

## Security
- **No secrets in code.** All API keys and secrets come from `process.env` (e.g. CLOUDCONVERT_API_KEY, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY, ADMIN_PASSWORD_MANU2, ENCRYPTION_KEY). Never commit keys.
- **Admin routes** (e.g. /api/admin/*) are gated by header `x-admin-password` vs env ADMIN_PASSWORD_MANU2.
- **Free PDF tools** (Compressor, Print Optimizer) run **client-side only** (no file upload to server); only lead-capture (email) hits the API for Compressor.
- **File size:** Vercel serverless body limit 4.5 MB. Tools that accept uploads cap at 4 MB or use direct-to-CloudConvert upload (paid flows).

## Cost & product
- **Free tools** must not use CloudConvert (use client-side or email-only APIs). See `docs/FREE-TOOLS-COST.md`.
- **Paid tools:** $7 per use or $27 for 6 months. Verify via verify-access (downloadId payment_confirmed or subscription), then PaymentGate on download page.
- **Positioning:** KDP-focused; "upload → KDP-ready". Reasonable pricing; cost-aware.

## Key paths
- Checker: `src/app/api/kdp-pdf-check`, `src/app/kdp-pdf-checker`, report on `src/app/download/[id]` (source=checker).
- KDP Formatter (DOCX→PDF): `src/app/api/kdp-format-docx`, `src/lib/kdpPdfGenerator.ts`, `src/lib/kdpDocxParser.ts`.
- Format Review (planned): `docs/KDP-FORMAT-REVIEW-APP.md`, `docs/KDP-FORMAT-REVIEW-RENDER-AND-SKILLS.md`; not yet built; listed as "Coming soon" on formatter page.
